// Unified bridge-token extraction. Replaces the three separate
// extract*Tokens functions that index.ts defined inline. Covers:
//
//   <<SEND_FILE:abs-path>>      — existing
//   <<SCHEDULE:time|prompt>>    — existing
//   <<ASK:question_id|...>>     — existing
//   <<SKILL_USED:name|reason>>  — new (AB-1)
//   <<GOAL_DONE:reason>>        — new (AB-1)
//
// Token syntax, limits, and semantics are defined by
// `docs/ab-token-protocol.md`. This module is the one extraction path —
// no parallel implementations anywhere.
//
// Design notes:
//
//  • Code-region masking is mandatory for every regex. Agents frequently
//    paste token examples inside ``` fenced or `inline` code blocks to
//    explain the protocol; without masking those examples would be
//    treated as live tokens and accidentally trigger real side effects.
//    The mask/restore pair lives here and is private — callers don't
//    need to know about sentinels.
//
//  • ASK parsing keeps its full-featured parseAskInner function inline
//    here so SKILL_USED's simpler parser can sit next to it. The
//    Telegram-UI layer (buildAskKeyboard / askRegistry / replyWithAsk)
//    stays in index.ts — that's not transformation, it's rendering.
//
//  • SCHEDULE's time-parsing dependencies (parseDuration,
//    parseAbsoluteTime, parseRecurrence, computeNextRunAt) are injected
//    via the `scheduleParsers` parameter of `transform()` so this file
//    doesn't pull in the whole schedule-store module graph.

